<h3 class="date"><a href="/2005/dec/20/">&#x27a0;</a> December 20, 2005</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="teaching_intelligent_design_in" >

        
        <a name="002173"></a>
        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://www.pamd.uscourts.gov/kitzmiller/kitzmiller_342.pdf">Teaching &quot;Intelligent Design&quot; in US public schools is unconstitutional [PDF]</a></h4>

        

        <p>The 139-page ruling.  My favourite bit starts on page 31, and explains how &#8220;Of Pandas And People&#8221; (the &#8220;textbook&#8221; that kids in Dover were supposed to read as part of their biology class) had the word &#8220;creationism&#8221; search-n-replaced to &#8220;intelligent design&#8221; after the 1987 ruling saying teaching &#8220;creationism&#8221; was unconstitutional.  These fundamentalist fuckwits are shameless.</p>

        <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span10">
                
